The court has made these participation directions for the following reasons:

they are a proportionate way to meet the apparent needs of [name];

they protect both parties from coercive conduct or false allegations of coercive conduct;

[other reasons].

These participation directions have been made by the court without receiving representations from all parties. An application may be made to set aside, vary or stay them provided it is issued within seven days of service of this order.

